Dia. 01 If Black Plays
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par When one is counting how much a move is worth, it is convenient to distinguish the difference between Black's turn and White's turn. That difference is the worth of the move.
\par
\par Let's check what happens if it is Black's turn in this situation.
\par If Black plays at 1, Black's territory hasn't increased, right?
\par
\par
\par }
