Dia. 02 If White's turn
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue255;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Let's check what happens if White plays.
\par
\par If White plays at 1, White gets \cf1\b 1 point \cf0\b0 at A. There is no change in Black's territory.
\par
\par Therefore Black 1 in \b Dia. 01\b0  and White 1 in this diagram \cf2\b worth 1 point\cf0\b0 .
\par
\par
\par }
